# DAX Measures Documentation

All key DAX measures used in the Customer Churn Analytics Dashboard.

---

## Core Churn Metrics

```dax
-- Total Customers
Total Customers = COUNTROWS(Customers)

-- Total Churned
Total Churned = 
COUNTROWS(FILTER(Customers, Customers[Churned] = "Yes"))

-- Total Retained
Total Retained = 
COUNTROWS(FILTER(Customers, Customers[Churned] = "No"))

-- Overall Churn Rate
Churn Rate = 
DIVIDE([Total Churned], [Total Customers], 0)

-- Retention Rate
Retention Rate = 
DIVIDE([Total Retained], [Total Customers], 0)
```

---

## Segment Analysis

```dax
-- Churn Rate for Selected Segment
Churn Rate Segment = 
DIVIDE(
    CALCULATE([Total Churned]),
    CALCULATE([Total Customers]),
    0
)

-- Churn Rate vs Average (for conditional formatting)
Churn vs Average = 
[Churn Rate Segment] - CALCULATE([Churn Rate], ALL(Customers[Segment]))
```

---

## Revenue Impact

```dax
-- Revenue at Risk (churned customers)
Revenue at Risk = 
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Customers[MonthlyCharges]),
    Customers[Churned] = "Yes"
)

-- Retained Revenue
Retained Revenue = 
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Customers[MonthlyCharges]),
    Customers[Churned] = "No"
)

-- Average Revenue per Churned Customer
Avg Revenue Churned = 
DIVIDE([Revenue at Risk], [Total Churned], 0)
```

---

## Trend Analysis

```dax
-- Churn Rate Previous Period
Churn Rate Previous = 
CALCULATE(
    [Churn Rate],
    PREVIOUSMONTH(Dates[Date])
)

-- Churn Rate Change (MoM)
Churn Rate Change = 
[Churn Rate] - [Churn Rate Previous]
```

---

## Tenure Bands

```dax
-- Tenure Band (Calculated Column)
Tenure Band = 
SWITCH(
    TRUE(),
    Customers[Tenure] <= 6,   "0-6 Months",
    Customers[Tenure] <= 12,  "6-12 Months",
    Customers[Tenure] <= 24,  "1-2 Years",
    "2+ Years"
)
```
